<h1 class="h1"> Rules and Regulations</h1>
<div class="about-section">
    <h2>The Students</h2>
    <p class="rules">
        1. They should be regular to school, neatly dressed in the prescribed school uniform. <br>
        2. They should be ready with all the required learning material as per the daily timetable. <br>
        3. They should be attentive in  class, take down notes on the lessons taught during each period, and read each day's lesson at least twice at home <br>
        4. They should  note the assignments given, in the school diary, complete and submit the same on date.<br>
        5. They should be honest, truthful, loyal, orderly & hard working. <br>
        6. They should be polite to everyone, show due respect to others and maintain self-respect <br>
        7. They should learn what is right and just and avoid the company of undesirable elements: desist from gossiping and tale-bearing  ; nor should they allow themselves to be misguided by others. <br>
         </p>
  </div>
  <div class="about-section">
    <h2>Code of Conduct</h2>
    <p class="content-paragraph">
      The school expects all the students to maintain a high standard of discipline. Pragathi, being an English medium school, expects students to communicate in English during school hours. They should be well-mannered and considerate of the needs of others, displaying courtesy at all times. They should be dedicated to their academics and actively participate in co-curricular and extracurricular activities. Violation of any of the conduct guidelines is subject to appropriate punishment as determined by the school. Serious offenses, such as immoral behavior, engaging in physical fights or brawls within or outside the school campus, damaging or defacing school property, or engaging in forgery, can result in suspension or dismissal.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="about-section">
    <h2>Discipline</h2>
    <p class="rules">
        <li class="points">Students are expected to be regular in attendance and academics, obedient and respectful, and avoid malpractice during tests and examinations. If any student is found indulging in unfair means during examinations, he/she will be awarded zero in that particular paper. </li>
        <li class="points">Students must be on time for the Morning Assembly.</li>
        <li class="points">Students are not permitted to leave the classroom without proper reasons and written permission. On any account, if a student has to go home during school hours from school he/she must get written permission from the school authority</li>
        <li class="points"> Respect for school property is a moral obligation and any damage to it must be made good by the student concerned. </li>
        <li class="points">caps may be worn only out in the sun but not in the classroom.</li>
        <li class="points">Chewing gum on school premises is prohibited.</li> 
        <li class="points">Graffiti and defacing walls, desks and toilets will be dealt with severly. </li>
        <li class="points">Forging parent's signature and changing marks or entries in report cards may warrant suspension</li>
        <li class="points">No student can bring an outsider to school and arrange meetings or engage them to fight against students of the school. </li>
        <li class="points">Bunking class or being found out side the school during school hours will be severely dealt with.</li>
        <li class="points">The use of foul and objectionable language is unacceptable.</li>
        <li class="points">Stealing of any kind is a serious offense.</li>
        <li class="points">No collective petitions of students will be entertained. However personal grievances can be addressed individually with the Class Teacher, incharge or Principal. </li>
        <li class="points">Carrying mobile phones,ipads, any other unnecessary electronic devices is strictly prohibited.if any child is found with these devices,or with money, cameras,etc .the same will be confiscated</li>    
    </p>
  </div>
