<div class="about-section">
  <h2>Attendance Policy:</h2>
   <p class="uniform">
    <h4 class="attendence">1. Attendance Requirements:</h4>
    <li class="points">All students are expected to attend classes regularly and punctually.</li>
    <li class="points">Regular attendance is essential for academic success and to fully engage in the learning process.</li>
    <h4 class="attendence">2. Reporting Absences:</h4>
    <li class="points">Parents/guardians are required to report student absences to the school as soon as possible.</li>
    <li class="points">Absences can be reported through the designated attendance hotline, email, or an online attendance reporting system.</li>
    <li class="points">Provide specific contact information for reporting absences.</li>
    <h4 class="attendence">3. Excused Absences:</h4>
    <li class="points">Excused absences include but are not limited to illness, medical appointments, religious observances, family emergencies, and school-approved activities.</li>
    <li class="points">To have an absence considered excused, parents/guardians must provide appropriate documentation or request prior approval from the school.</li>
    <h4 class="attendence">4. Unexcused Absences:</h4>
    <li class="points">Unexcused absences refer to absences without a valid reason or proper authorization.</li>
    <li class="points">Consequences for unexcused absences may include disciplinary actions, grade deductions, or loss of privileges.</li>
    <li class="points">After a certain number of unexcused absences, parents/guardians and students may be required to attend a meeting with school administration to address the issue.</li>
    <h4 class="attendence">5. Tardiness:</h4>
    <li class="points">Students are expected to arrive on time for all classes.</li>
    <li class="points">Late arrivals may be marked as tardy, and repeated tardiness may result in disciplinary consequences.</li>
    <h4 class="attendence">6. Attendance Records:</h4>
    <li class="points">Attendance records are maintained by the school administration and may be reviewed by parents/guardians upon request.</li>
    <li class="points">Attendance reports may be used for academic evaluation, eligibility for participation in extracurricular activities, and reporting to relevant authorities if required by law.</li>
    <h4 class="attendence">7. Make-Up Work:</h4>
    <li class="points">Students are responsible for making up any missed assignments, classwork, or assessments due to absences.</li>
    <li class="points">Teachers will provide guidelines and reasonable time frames for completing make-up work.</li>
    <li class="points">It is the student's responsibility to communicate with teachers to obtain missed assignments and arrange for make-up work.</li>
    <h4 class="attendence"> 8. Academic Progress Monitoring:</h4>
    <li class="points">Teachers and school staff will regularly monitor students' academic progress and provide feedback to support their growth. Students are expected to actively review and reflect upon feedback provided and make necessary improvements.</li>
    <h4 class="attendence"> 9.Utilizing Available Resources:</h4>
    <li class="points">Students are encouraged to utilize the resources provided by the school, such as libraries, research materials, online databases, and academic support services.</li>
    <li class="points">Seeking assistance from teachers, counselors, or tutors when needed is highly recommended to enhance academic performance and overcome challenges.</li>
  </p>
